      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ الْحَسَدَ يَأْكُلُ الْإِيمَانَ كَمَا تَأْكُلُ النَّارُ الْحَطَبَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Khalid and Al Husayn Bin Saeed, from Al Nazar Bin Suweyd, from Al Qasim Bin Suleyman, from Jarrah al Madainy, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The envy consumes the <span class=\"iTxt\">Emān</span> just as the fire consumes the firewood’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. It is narrated from him (narrator of the Hadith above) from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn Khalid and al-Husayn ibn Sa’id from al-Nadr ibn Suwayd from al-Qasim ibn Sulayman from Jarrah al-Mada’ini from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “Envy consumes belief just as fire consumes firewood.” "
        ]
      }
    }
